From: Kalesh AP <kalesh-anakkur.purayil@broadcom.com>
Date: Thu, 14 Aug 2025 16:55:54 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 1/1] RDMA/bnxt_re: Delete always true SGID table check
Git-commit: 4a9fba4d008a0d395407224f18def611ee85ba09
Patch-mainline: v6.18-rc1
References: jsc#PED-15349

The "sgid_tbl" inside "rdev->qplib_res" is a static memory.
Hence, the check always return true.

Signed-off-by: Kalesh AP <kalesh-anakkur.purayil@broadcom.com>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20250814112555.221665-9-kalesh-anakkur.purayil@broadcom.com
Signed-off-by: Leon Romanovsky <leon@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Nicolas Morey <nmorey@suse.com>
---
 drivers/infiniband/hw/bnxt_re/ib_verbs.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/infiniband/hw/bnxt_re/ib_verbs.c b/drivers/infiniband/hw/bnxt_re/ib_verbs.c
index 98bc8b6290f1..195a9ba6f65d 100644
--- a/drivers/infiniband/hw/bnxt_re/ib_verbs.c
+++ b/drivers/infiniband/hw/bnxt_re/ib_verbs.c
@@ -375,7 +375,7 @@ int bnxt_re_del_gid(const struct ib_gid_attr *attr, void **context)
 	if (!ctx)
 		return -EINVAL;
 
-	if (sgid_tbl && sgid_tbl->active) {
+	if (sgid_tbl->active) {
 		if (ctx->idx >= sgid_tbl->max)
 			return -EINVAL;
 		gid_to_del = &sgid_tbl->tbl[ctx->idx].gid;
